  Locus:
    Page: 317
    Verse: 12
Tags:
  - Mind
---
The mind is the mischief-maker. It jumps from doubt to doubt; it puts
obstacles in the way. It weaves a net and gets entangled in it. It is ever
discontented; it runs after a hundred things and away from another hundred.
